               <fromdate standarddate="1966">1966</fromdate>
               <todate standarddate="1966">1966</todate>
            </daterange>
         </unitdatestructured>
         <abstract id="aspace_b1c5adbd9b878c0a746311f2593d25fe">The materials consist of 16mm motion picture film and soundtracks used in the production of <emph render="italic">To Be A Man</emph>, a Yale admissions film.</abstract>
    
      </did>
      <odd id="aspace_1914f9b5598c26ffd3f620f1a4c5ea8e">
         <head>General note</head>
         <p>Forms part of Yale Record Group 48-B (YRG 48-B), Yale audiovisual records and collections.</p>  
      </odd>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_443d3241a3cb7974f6f7e1fa3fec7952">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research. Original audiovisual materials, as well as preservation and duplicating masters, may not be played. Researchers must consult use copies, or if none exist must pay for a use copy, which is retained by the repository. Researchers wishing to obtain an additional copy for their personal use should consult Copying Services information on the Manuscripts and Archives web site.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_0fc119dc789d23f3cf4ce22ac6350a99">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>
            <emph render="italic">To Be A Man</emph> Motion Picture Film, Yale University (RU 845). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <processinfo id="aspace_ee3321fb6e965ecbf905575fae26283e">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_0b3995b48415b381c42d5da80c704504">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The materials consist of 16mm motion picture film and soundtracks used in the production of <emph render="italic">To Be A Man</emph>, a Yale admissions film.</p>
         <p>The final product produced for distribution is catalogued individually.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_0be50095585ae5bb2d9f3568d5a0603d">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by type of record.</p>  
      </arrangement>
